-- 
Kenyan Sugar Prices Jump Ahead of Plant Maintenance, Business Daily Says

-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 
2011-06-28T04:53:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-28/kenyan-sugar-prices-jump-ahead-of-plant-maintenance-business-daily-says.html
Sugar prices in  Kenya  have surged as
much as 39 percent as several mills prepare to shut down for
their annual factory maintenance, Business Daily reported.  Retail prices jumped to as high as 250 shillings ($2.75)
per 2-kilogram (4.4-pound) pack last week, compared with 180
shillings a week earlier, the Nairobi-based newspaper said,
citing managers at retail outlets including Woolmart
Supermarket.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eric Ombok in Nairobi at 
 eombok@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Richardson in Nairobi at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net . 